Ibrahim Rotich, the prime suspect in the murder of Olympian Agnes Tirop, will remain in police custody for 20 more days pending conclusion of investigations. Rotich, who was the husband to the deceased, was arraigned before Magistrate Charles Kutwa where the prosecution sought for more time to detain him. The court directed that the accused be detained at Railways Police Station in Eldoret. He will also undergo a mental assessment at Eldoret Teaching and Referral Hospital. The case will be mentioned on November 9. Tirop was stabbed to death in her house in Iten, Elgeyo Marakwet County. Her husband, who had gone missing after the incident, would later be arrested in Changwamwe, Mombasa. Also Read: Accoridng to the DCI, Rotich was nabbed while trying to flee to a neighboring country to evade justice. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam